The Permanent Secretary in the Rivers State Primary Health Care Management Management Board (RSPHCMB) Dr. Agiriye Monima Harry, has stated that heading the agency is a long-term dream as it affords him the opportunity to serve the public in different dimensions. Dr. Harry, who is a Nigerian trained Medical practitioner with specialty in Orthopaedic Medicine, has dedicated almost the last two decades of his life into the Rivers State Civil Service. At a recent event while speaking with journalists, he stated that, “Leading RSPHCMB is a dream come true” for him and he was ready to put in more work to take the agency to greater heights. Between January 2004 to January 2006, he was head of department, Accident and Emergency, BMSH. Coordinator of River State Emergency Medical Services from April 2003 through October 2007; and director of River State Emergency Medical Services from October 2007 through 2013. Director of medical service, River State Ministry of Health from May 2013 through July 2013; director of special programmes at River State Emergency Medical Services from July 2013 through August 2015; appointed permanent secretary Rivers State Primary Health Care Management Board (RSPHCMB) on August 2015. For Dr. Harry, his time in the civil service is an opportunity to serve humanity and make the world a better place which has attracted numerous awards and Professional Certifications such as Instructor basic trauma life support, Fellow of Arbeitsgemein shaft fur osteosynthesfragen(AO) International, Instructor Advanced Trauma Life Support amongst others. His rise through the ranks within the service is a testament of his dedication and a morale booster to many around him.